  "text": "We show in Lemma 40 that transducts of morphic sequences are morphic. In order to prove this, we also need several lemmas about transducers which are of independent interest. The approach here is adapted from a result in Allouche and Shallit [CITATION_1] ; it is attributed in that book to Dekking. We repeat it here partly for the convenience of the reader, but mostly because there are some details of the proof which are used in the analysis of the substitutivity property.",
